      "IP evacuated to shore for further evaluation after consultation with onshore medical personnel",
      "IP underwent surgery"
    ],
    "summary": "On 27 September 2024, a Deckhand on the M/V Harvey Freedom support vessel injured his leg during equipment back-loading operations from the Noble Valiant drillship. While attempting to steady a 50-foot basket with a tagline as it was being landed, the support vessel rolled causing the IP to lose footing and injure his left leg. The IP was evacuated to the drillship, then to shore, required surgery, and resulted in more than 3-days lost time.",
